<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
A very rare species in Greece, having been collected only three times from the floristic regions of North Central (NC), South Pindos (SPi) and Sterea Ellas (StE; 
<bibRefCitation author="Georgiou, O." journalOrPublisher="Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668173" refString="Georgiou, O., 1997. Flora Hellenica 1. Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein" title="Flora Hellenica 1" year="1997">Georgiou 1997</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pirini, C." journalOrPublisher="Phytologia Balcanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="109 - 129" refId="B7669198" refString="Pirini, C., Tsiripidis, I., Karagiannakidou, V., Raus, T., Babalonas, D., 2010. Pseudo-steppic and aquatic flora of the Natura 2000 network site Limnes Vegoritida-Petron (North-Central Greece). Phytologia Balcanica 16 (1): 109 - 129" title="Pseudo-steppic and aquatic flora of the Natura 2000 network site Limnes Vegoritida-Petron (North-Central Greece)" volume="16" year="2010">Pirini et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Hayek, A." journalOrPublisher="Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis. Centralblatt fuer Sammlung und Veroffentlichung von Einzeldiagnosen neuer Pflanzen. Beihefte" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="1 - 1201" refId="B7679176" refString="Hayek, A., 1927. Prodromus florae peninsulae balcanicae. Band 1 Pteridophyta, Gymnospermae, Dicotyledoneae (Apetalae et Choripetalae). Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis. Centralblatt fuer Sammlung und Veroffentlichung von Einzeldiagnosen neuer Pflanzen. Beihefte 30 (1): 1 - 1201" title="Prodromus florae peninsulae balcanicae. Band 1 Pteridophyta, Gymnospermae, Dicotyledoneae (Apetalae et Choripetalae)" volume="30" year="1927">Hayek (1927)</bibRefCitation>
reported it from Thraki (Thrace), but without any further information regarding its locality. Therefore, it is not known whether this reference should be attributed to the Greek, Turkish or Bulgarian part of the territory. The above-cited collection confirms the existence of the species in the Greek part of Thraki and consequently, adds a new floristic record to the NE region.
</paragraph>
